      "span_text": "Our data are in agreement with those of Ting et al,  who evaluated 102 limbs with mixed superficial and deep reflux before and after saphenous ablation and found that superficial femoral vein reflux disappeared in about 28% of segments and popliteal vein reflux was eliminated in 28% of segments."
